05:06.208 --> 05:07.999
Strumpet.

05:30.083 --> 05:32.499
You're a lifesaver,
you know that, Belle?

05:32.750 --> 05:33.624
Thanks.

05:38.833 --> 05:40.249
Deanna wants to talk to you.

05:41.041 --> 05:42.582
What makes you say that, Belle?

05:42.833 --> 05:45.415
She just was telling me...
- If Deanna wants to talk to me,

05:45.666 --> 05:47.165
she'll come and talk to me.

05:48.291 --> 05:50.499
I'll take one of those burgers
when those burgers are ready.

05:50.750 --> 05:53.624
Are these burgers ready yet, Belle?
- I don't...

05:54.208 --> 05:56.790
I'll check.
- Good.

05:57.291 --> 05:58.624
Hey, keep an eye on Darlin'.

05:58.875 --> 06:01.332
She's after that Clapp boy again.

06:09.000 --> 06:10.999
Deanna.
- Chris.

06:15.958 --> 06:17.832
So, what's on your mind, sweetheart?

06:18.583 --> 06:21.249
I told you! No more kissing.

06:21.500 --> 06:23.499
It is inappropriate.
Do you hear me?

06:23.750 --> 06:26.124
Yeah, I hear you,
you're yelling in my ear.

06:26.375 --> 06:28.540
Can I have my radio back now?
- We'll see.

06:28.791 --> 06:31.290
What are you gonna do, jenny?
- Hold her. - Stop it!

06:31.541 --> 06:32.999
Are you gonna cry
to your Momma, like a baby?

06:33.250 --> 06:34.999
What's the matter, Jenny?
- You wearing diapers?

06:35.250 --> 06:36.290
Let's see it!

06:36.541 --> 06:37.915
Stop it! I'm gonna tell!

06:38.166 --> 06:39.624
Like a girl, you're gonna tell.

06:39.875 --> 06:41.249
You need your diaper changed, jenny.

06:42.708 --> 06:44.332
Ow!
- Shut up!

06:45.166 --> 06:47.332
Diapers? Diapers, Jenny?

06:49.000 --> 06:52.832
I spend as much time as I can
with Ed up at the home,

06:53.125 --> 06:55.290
but I'd like to spend more.

06:55.541 --> 06:57.124
That's understandable.

06:57.541 --> 06:59.499
So what I wanna do is...

06:59.750 --> 07:02.124
I wanna sell it all off,
get myself a nice little

07:02.375 --> 07:04.374
one-bedroom up around there,

07:04.625 --> 07:07.707
so I can be with him
these last few months.

07:08.041 --> 07:10.915
I don't think he's got
much more than that.

07:13.625 --> 07:15.124
Hey.

07:16.000 --> 07:19.999
If you really wanted to sell,
I'm glad you came to me.

07:21.250 --> 07:24.332
So you just come by
the office on Monday

07:25.208 --> 07:28.707
and we'll start drawing up
some papers. Okay?

07:28.958 --> 07:30.874
I can't give you
the world for the place

07:31.125 --> 07:33.249
but I'll give you a fair price.

07:33.541 --> 07:36.165
I know you will, Chris.

07:36.583 --> 07:38.665
It's the good thing
about old friends,

07:38.916 --> 07:42.249
you don't have to worry
about gettin' a lube job.

07:50.416 --> 07:53.582
How'd you do, bud?
- Eight out of ten, dad.

07:55.791 --> 07:57.415
Consistently?

07:58.125 --> 08:00.665
The last one and once before that.

08:01.083 --> 08:03.499
I think I got the hang of it, though.

08:05.791 --> 08:08.624
Gotta hit your free throws
to win ball games.

08:08.875 --> 08:10.082
I know.

08:11.458 --> 08:13.540
That guy's got a major thing for Peg.

08:13.791 --> 08:16.374
He's pretty much a douche.
They went out like one time.

08:19.708 --> 08:20.957
Is that so?

08:36.625 --> 08:37.874
Watch the leather.

08:40.582 --> 08:41.999
So you didn't go in once, huh?

08:42.250 --> 08:44.290
Chlorine makes my hair gross.

08:45.916 --> 08:48.290
We wouldn't want that,
now, would we?

09:29.916 --> 09:32.124
You feed the dogs yet?

09:32.416 --> 09:34.457
Brian'll do it when he gets up.

09:35.166 --> 09:36.915
The dogs can wait.

09:48.958 --> 09:51.749
It's kinda nice when
it's quiet like this, isn't it?

13:29.500 --> 13:32.374
How's the average?
- 7 - 10.

13:32.625 --> 13:35.832
Pretty consistent.
- Good. That's good.

13:37.583 --> 13:39.249
Did you catch anything?

13:39.750 --> 13:41.832
Does it look like I got anything?

13:43.583 --> 13:45.457
I should turn down the ham.

13:45.708 --> 13:47.290
Fine, you do that,

13:47.791 --> 13:49.999
then come along with me, babe.

13:51.041 --> 13:52.540
Me too?

13:53.458 --> 13:55.624
Sure, sweetie. You too.

13:56.875 --> 13:58.540
Follow us, son!

14:23.083 --> 14:25.040
Watch your step.

14:28.458 --> 14:29.790
Okay.

14:30.416 --> 14:34.332
I want you guys to move
all this junk from the south end

14:34.583 --> 14:37.457
to the other side of the cellar,
and just sweep up the floor.

14:37.750 --> 14:40.915
Before dinner?
- Yes, before dinner, Peg.

14:41.166 --> 14:42.249
Why?

14:42.500 --> 14:44.249
Because your dad asked you to.

14:44.500 --> 14:46.832
You don't have a problem with that,
do you Brian? - No.

14:47.083 --> 14:48.749
Where do you want us
to move all the stuff?

14:49.000 --> 14:50.124
In the dump trailer.

14:50.375 --> 14:53.124
If it's small and burnable,
put it in the burn barrel.

14:53.375 --> 14:56.749
You're gonna need some gloves.
There's a couple pair in the barn.

14:57.000 --> 14:59.874
Have you fed the dogs yet?
- It's Peggy's turn. I had morning.

15:00.125 --> 15:01.415
Peg?

15:01.666 --> 15:04.749
Fine. I'll feed the dogs.
I'll go get the gloves.

15:05.166 --> 15:07.165
Is there mice down here?

15:08.500 --> 15:09.499
Could be.

15:09.875 --> 15:11.749
Should I get some cheese?

15:12.083 --> 15:14.499
No, I don't think
that's a very good idea.

15:14.750 --> 15:17.040
Belle, you organize
things around here.

15:17.375 --> 15:19.582
With three of you,
it shouldn't take very long.

15:19.833 --> 15:22.207
I've got some things
to do at the house.

15:22.916 --> 15:24.290
Chris?

15:26.000 --> 15:27.374
Why are we doing this?

15:28.916 --> 15:30.707
You'll see.

15:31.416 --> 15:33.040
Trust me on this one.

16:12.916 --> 16:14.874
What's he doing?

16:15.125 --> 16:17.457
Peggy, you scared
the hell out of me.

16:17.708 --> 16:20.207
Sorry. I couldn't sleep.

16:20.458 --> 16:23.290
Well, try. You have
school in the morning.

16:24.791 --> 16:26.499
What's dad doing?

16:29.666 --> 16:31.332
Go to bed, Peggy.

16:34.000 --> 16:35.582
It's late.

16:46.000 --> 16:47.290
Good night, mom.

16:47.583 --> 16:49.165
Good night, honey.

17:26.875 --> 17:28.582
Hey, I don't wanna hurt you!

17:41.291 --> 17:43.999
Okay, so who can tell me
what a scalene triangle is?

17:44.375 --> 17:46.790
Three unequal sides.
- That's right.

17:47.041 --> 17:49.499
But we forgot to raise our
hand again, didn't we, jackie?

17:50.125 --> 17:51.249
Sorry, Miss Raton.

17:51.500 --> 17:53.957
So what other kinds of triangles
are there? Name them for me, guys.

17:57.541 --> 17:58.624
Peggy?

17:58.875 --> 18:01.165
Taking copious notes as usual, right?

18:01.416 --> 18:02.665
Just some notes, yeah.

18:02.916 --> 18:04.665
So what other kinds
of triangles are there, Peg?

18:05.166 --> 18:06.249
Scalene?

18:07.541 --> 18:08.790
Guys.

18:09.041 --> 18:10.457
Please, may I be excused?

18:10.791 --> 18:12.624
Yes. Of course you may.

18:45.166 --> 18:46.915
You okay, sweetie?

18:47.166 --> 18:50.499
Yeah. I just had to come
and get my stuff.

18:53.541 --> 18:55.290
Sorry.

19:02.833 --> 19:04.457
Great shot, Cyndi!

19:06.916 --> 19:08.499
Way to go, Brian!

19:18.791 --> 19:19.790
You're too good.

20:11.500 --> 20:12.665
What's up, Cyndi?

20:12.916 --> 20:15.374
There's something sticky
like glue in my brush.

20:15.625 --> 20:16.207
Let me see.

20:18.000 --> 20:18.999
Gum.

20:20.000 --> 20:21.624
It's okay Cyndi. I'll help you.

20:21.875 --> 20:24.249
Ow! That hurts!
- Sorry.

20:24.875 --> 20:26.207
It's okay. Thanks for trying.

20:28.083 --> 20:29.374
Dammit!

22:08.916 --> 22:09.999
Fuck!

22:57.791 --> 23:01.040
That is not civilized behavior!

23:05.250 --> 23:06.457
Fuck!

23:08.416 --> 23:09.290
Dammit!

23:13.625 --> 23:14.624
Fuck!

23:34.291 --> 23:35.874
Oh, God!

24:11.166 --> 24:12.165
So...

24:13.000 --> 24:14.665
you like to bite.

24:17.916 --> 24:21.082
You can't understand
a word I'm saying.

24:21.333 --> 24:22.790
I get that.

24:24.375 --> 24:26.165
But I'll bet that you could guess...

24:27.833 --> 24:31.165
that I am more than just a little bit
upset with you right now.

24:32.833 --> 24:34.457
So I need to make sure

24:34.708 --> 24:38.082
that you understand
just who is in charge here.

24:53.416 --> 24:55.832
I've got kids to raise
around here, lady.

24:57.958 --> 25:02.540
And disobedience is not something
I want them to witness.

25:08.250 --> 25:10.207
They're very good kids,

25:11.333 --> 25:15.790
and I would very much like
to introduce them to you.

25:16.041 --> 25:17.540
But...

25:18.041 --> 25:20.415
if you're not going to be nice,

25:24.000 --> 25:26.957
if you are going
to be disobedient,

25:29.958 --> 25:32.082
then I can't do that.

25:32.458 --> 25:33.790
Now can I?

25:37.625 --> 25:40.540
Plus, I need to feel better
about losing my finger.

25:57.125 --> 25:59.165
Okay, I'm gonna go
to the house for a minute.

25:59.416 --> 26:00.665
I'm gonna bring the wife and kids.

26:02.916 --> 26:04.749
And you be nice.

26:07.583 --> 26:08.957
Be nice.

26:25.875 --> 26:29.124
I feel better about
losing my finger now.

26:38.166 --> 26:39.624
One shot.

26:40.375 --> 26:42.040
I heard you.
What were you shootin' at?

26:42.291 --> 26:43.499
You'll see.

26:46.125 --> 26:48.457
What is that new tune?
Where is it from?

26:48.916 --> 26:50.540
Korea.

26:50.791 --> 26:52.082
Korea?

26:53.333 --> 26:55.290
I like it.
- Me too.

26:56.541 --> 26:58.582
You'll spoil your dinner.

26:58.916 --> 27:00.249
Not a chance.

27:00.500 --> 27:02.957
You say that now.
- I certainly do.

27:03.500 --> 27:04.999
Okay everybody.

27:06.375 --> 27:08.499
Who wants to go down
to the cellar with me?

27:10.041 --> 27:12.040
What do you have in there?
A mountain lion?

27:13.166 --> 27:16.207
This is a hell of a lot better
than a mountain lion, son.

27:21.000 --> 27:22.624
Dad?

27:24.416 --> 27:26.082
What is this?

27:27.250 --> 27:30.415
God only knows
where she's been living, Peg.

27:31.041 --> 27:33.790
In the woods. In caves.

27:34.791 --> 27:36.040
We're gonna help her.

27:36.541 --> 27:39.040
She needs a big Band Aid.

27:39.958 --> 27:41.040
That's right.

27:41.291 --> 27:42.957
That's the first thing
we're gonna fix.

27:43.208 --> 27:44.624
She's been wounded.

27:44.875 --> 27:46.082
We'll get right to it. Okay.

27:46.333 --> 27:50.624
We are all going to have to share in
the responsibility of taking care of her.

27:50.875 --> 27:52.290
Ground rules.

27:53.583 --> 27:55.249
No touching.

27:55.500 --> 27:58.207
I learned the hard way
that our friend here likes to bite.

27:58.458 --> 28:00.124
She bit you?

28:00.375 --> 28:03.749
She took an inch off my finger.
Swallowed it.

28:04.791 --> 28:06.207
Jesus!

28:06.833 --> 28:08.832
What are we gonna do with her?

28:09.375 --> 28:11.415
We're gonna train her, Brian.

28:11.750 --> 28:13.249
Civilize her.

28:13.583 --> 28:16.749
Free her from herself,
from her baser instincts.

28:17.000 --> 28:18.874
This woman thinks
that she is an animal.

28:19.125 --> 28:20.499
And God only knows
how she got that way,

28:20.750 --> 28:22.915
but we cannot have people
running around the woods

28:23.166 --> 28:24.749
thinking they're animals.
It isn't right.

28:25.000 --> 28:26.665
It's not safe.

28:31.958 --> 28:32.957
Belle?

28:34.833 --> 28:35.957
Yes?

28:36.208 --> 28:39.374
Could you run up and
put together a bowl of cereal

28:39.625 --> 28:41.957
or oatmeal or something simple?

28:43.208 --> 28:45.540
She's gotta be hungry.
The only thing she's had to eat

28:45.791 --> 28:47.665
since I captured her is...

28:48.166 --> 28:49.832
Your finger.

28:54.250 --> 28:57.290
And Peg? Go up
and get the first-aid kit.

28:57.541 --> 28:59.582
I wanna see to her wounds.

29:00.000 --> 29:01.082
Okay?

29:01.333 --> 29:02.624
Okay, let's go, girls. Come on.

29:04.208 --> 29:05.999
Better than a mountain lion, son?

29:06.250 --> 29:09.165
Do we really get to keep her?
- We do.

29:15.750 --> 29:18.499
Now, I cannot stress this enough.

29:18.750 --> 29:23.374
For the moment,
everyone keep your distance.

29:24.291 --> 29:26.124
What is that, Belle?
Is that oatmeal?

29:26.375 --> 29:27.457
Yes.
- Good.

29:27.708 --> 29:28.832
Good. It's nice and nutritious.

29:29.083 --> 29:32.082
just go ahead
and set it down. Okay?

29:32.333 --> 29:34.790
So, Belle,
you're gonna set it down.

29:36.000 --> 29:38.165
But not too close. Good.

29:38.416 --> 29:39.957
And now, Brian,

29:41.041 --> 29:43.332
I want you to bring the rake.

29:45.333 --> 29:47.290
Okay. Now push it toward her.

29:48.625 --> 29:51.457
Be careful not to spill it.
Come on.

29:51.708 --> 29:53.040
There you go.

29:53.291 --> 29:55.624
Great. Great.
Everybody, that's teamwork.

29:55.875 --> 29:57.957
Okay? Everybody did their part.

30:05.666 --> 30:07.540
See what I mean about
keeping your distance?

30:09.416 --> 30:12.249
I guess next time
we need to use Rubbermaid.

30:13.458 --> 30:15.207
I'll clean it up. Alright.

30:20.833 --> 30:23.749
If she gets hungry enough, she'll eat.

30:24.250 --> 30:26.457
Okay, look, here,
huddle up. Here.

30:27.416 --> 30:31.665
This is our project
and it's a secret one.

30:32.458 --> 30:34.749
Now, I shouldn't
have to remind you

30:35.000 --> 30:37.040
to keep your mouths zipped,
but I'm doing it anyway.

30:38.208 --> 30:40.874
We're all gonna have to share
in chores with this one.

30:41.125 --> 30:43.290
It's the same as
taking care of the dogs.

30:43.541 --> 30:46.957
Someone's gonna have to
clean up after her and so on.

30:47.208 --> 30:50.615
Your mother and I
will take care of anything...

30:50.833 --> 30:53.457
overly complicated. Right, hon?

30:53.958 --> 30:55.415
Yes.

30:57.250 --> 30:59.540
Okay, then. Well, dinner time.

30:59.791 --> 31:02.207
She may not be hungry,
but I am.

31:02.458 --> 31:04.124
Okay. We'll work out
the details later, okay?

31:04.375 --> 31:06.540
Let's go eat.
Is everybody okay with that?

31:06.791 --> 31:09.374
Everybody okay? Yeah?
Okay. Let's go.

31:39.958 --> 31:41.499
Some salt?

32:00.875 --> 32:02.374
Are you in there?

32:04.500 --> 32:07.290
Well, when I'm sad
I listen to my radio.

32:07.541 --> 32:09.165
Wanna hear?

33:50.833 --> 33:53.082
How are things at school, kiddo?

33:54.291 --> 33:55.665
Fine, dad.

34:08.916 --> 34:11.540
You're a good girl, Peg.

34:13.750 --> 34:18.206
And I know it's hard
sometimes being your age,

34:18.625 --> 34:23.123
but you've got to remember
to look at things on the bright side.

34:26.541 --> 34:29.540
You're gonna get
your license soon, right?

34:32.208 --> 34:34.456
Your grades are good, aren't they?

34:35.208 --> 34:36.665
Yeah.

34:39.000 --> 34:41.415
And you're gonna go to college.

34:45.541 --> 34:47.040
Think about that.

34:50.208 --> 34:51.790
Okay, dad.

35:03.166 --> 35:04.999
I love you, kiddo.

35:07.375 --> 35:09.457
I love you too, dad.

35:28.500 --> 35:29.832
Honey?

35:32.625 --> 35:34.082
That woman.

35:36.666 --> 35:39.457
Do you really think
we should be doing this?

35:58.791 --> 36:00.874
Let's go to bed, babe.

36:24.208 --> 36:26.540
Toby, how are you?
- Good morning. Perfect.

36:37.833 --> 36:39.457
Good morning, Mr. Cleek.

36:39.708 --> 36:40.874
Morning, Dorothy.

36:41.500 --> 36:44.874
So, how did it go with Mrs. Oldenberg?
Is she satisfied with the papers?

36:45.125 --> 36:47.290
Signed them right away.
- Fine, that's fine.

36:47.583 --> 36:50.040
You have lunch with Deanna
at noon, court at two,

36:50.291 --> 36:52.415
then a three-thirty
with the oil company reps.

36:52.666 --> 36:53.832
Are the Ludlow files ready?

36:54.083 --> 36:55.457
I just have to print out this last one.

36:55.708 --> 36:57.332
Okay, fine. Well, look,
when you're done with that,

36:57.583 --> 37:00.540
just bring 'em on in here,
along with another...

37:01.791 --> 37:04.207
cup of mud and
we'll get into it, okay?

37:04.458 --> 37:05.915
Thank you, Dorothy.

37:34.125 --> 37:37.915
Okay. First some stretching,
then eight laps, ladies.

37:39.208 --> 37:41.582
Tracy, pick up the stretcher.

37:47.041 --> 37:48.582
Not feeling well again today, Peg?

37:52.208 --> 37:53.874
There's something going on with her.

37:54.666 --> 37:57.207
This last month or so
she's really changed.

37:57.458 --> 37:58.915
They do at that age.

37:59.166 --> 38:01.540
Yeah, but you know how
they're all dressing these days,

38:01.791 --> 38:04.124
with the short skirts
and the skimpy blouses?

38:05.000 --> 38:05.999
Hadn't noticed it.

38:07.083 --> 38:10.165
Point is, that's how she
used to be too, you know?

38:10.416 --> 38:11.915
She's a very pretty girl.

38:12.166 --> 38:14.290
She ought to be...
- Flaunting it?

38:14.541 --> 38:16.999
Yeah. Dammit. Flaunting it.

38:17.250 --> 38:18.457
Did you flaunt it?

38:19.666 --> 38:22.665
I'd have made you pop
your fucking zipper, Mr. Wolf.

39:09.375 --> 39:10.749
Hey, Belle.

39:11.000 --> 39:13.040
Hi, Darlin'.
How are you two doing today?

39:14.208 --> 39:16.624
We're fine. You?

39:16.916 --> 39:20.707
Good. Yeah, we measured
Bonnie again this morning,

39:20.958 --> 39:23.290
and she has grown
half an inch already.

39:23.541 --> 39:25.582
Can you believe it? God!

39:25.833 --> 39:28.707
So, do you wanna barbecue
again some time soon?

39:29.291 --> 39:31.415
I don't see why not.

39:32.458 --> 39:34.957
The weather's been
perfect for it, hasn't it?

39:35.208 --> 39:38.457
Yeah. So, your place this time?

39:45.208 --> 39:47.957
The place is just a darn mess.

39:49.083 --> 39:52.957
Yeah, well, with all the little ones around,
how can it ever not be, right?

39:53.375 --> 39:54.582
Yeah.

39:54.833 --> 39:57.207
Hey, I gotta run.
See you soon, Vic.

39:57.458 --> 40:00.332
Okay. Listen, maybe I'll pop in
for a coffee sometime.

40:00.583 --> 40:01.957
Surprise you.

41:34.541 --> 41:35.707
So, after you finish that,

41:35.958 --> 41:37.915
would you please
send this to Deanna Plujack,

41:38.166 --> 41:40.165
and then we'll send
the initial check.

41:40.416 --> 41:41.457
Okay.
- Will do.

41:42.083 --> 41:43.957
Mr. Cleek,
may I say something?

41:44.583 --> 41:45.707
Of course, yeah.

41:45.958 --> 41:49.749
It's none of my business, really,
but in this economy,

41:50.000 --> 41:52.749
are you sure
you're not overextending?

41:53.541 --> 41:57.374
Have you ever known me to
let things get out of hand, Dorothy?

41:59.250 --> 42:02.499
No.

42:04.000 --> 42:07.040
That is a wonderful perfume.
That's new, isn't it?

42:07.500 --> 42:09.165
You like it?
- I do.

42:09.416 --> 42:11.457
I like it very much.
That's very nice. Yeah.

42:11.708 --> 42:12.790
Oh, no!
- Oh!

42:13.041 --> 42:14.499
